  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RECLAIM Sustainability! Mozambique-Tea</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to:
-Establish and strengthen regional and local multi stakeholder platforms (MSP) where civil society, public and private sector  engage collaboratively and form partnerships around the common good.
-Advocate towards the improvement or introduction of policies and/or enforcement on safety, healthcare, sexual reprodutive health services for female workers, environment, gender, trade and human rights.
-Improve bargaining position and equitable access to (digital) market intelligence for growers and workers as a result of new and innovative business models.
-Conduct regional campaigns on different and appropriate dissemination platforms to raise awareness on decent work, fair value distribution and sustainable resource management in the sector.</narrative>
  </description>
